The actual mechanic (this is the usable model)

Think in 3 layers:

1. Anchor (fixed)

Your core invariant

Example:

“Injured vets shouldn’t lose retirement.”

This never changes

⸻

2. Frames (variable)

Different ways to express it:

* Moral: “It’s wrong to punish service”
* Practical: “This is a fixable policy flaw”
* Identity: “We take care of our own”
* Contrast: “Other benefits exist—why not this?”

⸻

3. Oscillation (strategic)

You rotate frames depending on:

* audience
* context
* resistance

But always return to the same anchor.

⸻

Why this works

* The anchor builds recognition
* The frames create entry points
* The oscillation finds resonance

That’s how ideas spread without losing shape.

⸻

Where “luck” actually comes from

It’s not random.

It’s:

high repetition + good framing + correct timing

When those line up, it feels like luck.

